The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) South-West General Secretary Chief Rahman Owokoniran’s has said that his immediate focus is the unity and stability of the party and not contesting the Lagos State governorship election. Owokoniran said his primary interest is the unity of the party as the 2023 general elections draw close. ln a statement by his media aide, Mabel Oboh, Owonikoniran said a united PDP would signpost Nigeria’s deliverance from what he described as the misgovernance and anti-people policies of the All Progressives Congress(APC).   APC: Towards a successful convention     Oyebanji: competence not zoning should determine next Ekiti…     ‘Southeast should clinch APC presidential ticket’   “I have not shown interest in contesting the governorship election of Lagos State. Working for the unity of the party, especially with the election year very close, takes primacy over every other consideration right now. - Advertisement - “With a United Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, we will be able to answer Nigerians’ calls for deliverance from misgovernance and anti-people policies,” he said. Owokoniran added: “We, as a party, cannot afford to lose focus and disappoint Nigerians. And so any distraction must be avoided. “Lagos State occupies a seminal political, cultural and economic status. So any aspirant must be grounded, realistic and get all the backing available.”